				<pubDate>Thu, 14 Mar 2019 16:40:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Edna Granbo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2212713</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>No vote.<br /> This whole article is very lukewarm to me. The description was good, but footnotes 1-4 really drag on and add very little. The interview was bland and really wooden in some spots (footnote 5 is bad, and feels more like it's talking down to the reader). The last addendum doesn't do anything for me and is a really out of place student debt joke. This is a genially interesting concept that is brought down by quite a few things.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
